Install the Tor Browser in Linux Mint (Ubuntu), running the following command in the terminal:
from webupd8team repository

Terminal
Shekin@mylinuxmintpc~$
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/tor-browser
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install tor-browser

or from upubuntu repository

Terminal
Shekin@mylinuxmintpc~$
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:upubuntu-com/tor-bundle
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install tor-browser


To install an older distribution (Linux Mint 13/Ubuntu 12.10/12.04/11.10/) try these commands:

Terminal
Shekin@mylinuxmintpc~$
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:upubuntu-com/tor
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install tor-browser

Then you need to give permission to the current user (you) to use Tor-Brower following command:

Terminal
Shekin@mylinuxmintpc~$
sudo chown $USER-R ~/.tor-browser/


